        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The amount of total production of flexible polyurethane foam in 2018 in EU28 was of 1.7 million t, information taken from Austin, A. 2019. The European flexible PU foam market report for 2018. PU magazine vol 16, NO.4 - August/September 2019. The figures were provided by Europur. According to the article roughly half of the amount of MDI compared to TDI was consumed to produce flexible foam. Based on the amount of MDI/TDI consumed in the process, the split between MDI and TDI based polyurethane foams has been calculated. A 50/50 split was assumed among the two types of TDI products. 5% of overall foams are assumed to be flame retardant based on lack of data, assuming flame retardant foams belong to the "other" category in figure 2 of the article. 
</productionVolumeComment>
